        "visibleTableOrder": ["tblurNbhoPi1rdbC3", "tblsqD9jdCo1vfiv0"],
        "description": "## Welcome to the Employee directory template!\nUse this template to keep track of your employees' roles, hire dates, birthdays, phone numbers, and more. \n\nHere are some tips to help you get the most out of it:\n\n* Everything in an Airtable [base](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics#base) is customizable, including this description! You can add, edit, or remove any [tables](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#table), [fields](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#field), [records](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#record), or [views](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314) to fit your needs.\n* The Employee directory table has records with personal and professional details about each of your employees. Try adding a new employee record by clicking the plus button at the bottom of the list.\n* Each Department field is [linked](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502354#h_0c3d1a65-1f35-4e67-9b14-6213d4d2bca9) to a record in the Departments table, which you can use to list all of your company’s departments. Try clicking one of the blue department names in an employee’s record to quickly see more information about their department.\n* The On leave grid view is [filtered](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021501754-Getting-started-customizing-your-first-view#filters) to show records of employees who are currently out of office. Try changing the Status of one of these workers to Employee to filter them out of this view.\n* The Headshots [gallery view](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314-Getting-started-view-types) arranges your employee records into cards that feature a photo of them at the top, followed by their work and contact details below. Try adding their birthdays, too, by clicking Customize cards in the toolbar and switching the DOB field to visible.\n* Expand the [apps](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502434-Getting-started-building-blocks-for-success) dashboard for an employee organizational chart, a list of upcoming birthdays, and a timeline of when everybody joined the team. You can also reference the \"Read me 👋\" [description app](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F115013405088-Description-block) at any time to find out more information.\n\nExplore our [template gallery](https:\u002F\u002Fairtable.com\u002Ftemplates) for other example bases, or check out our [guide to getting started in Airtable](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics) to learn how to build a new base from scratch!",
