        "visibleTableOrder": ["tblIqQcamrbnYC3dR", "tbl4GLkzTfygPFeFu", "tbleHf1KM8aO97Law", "tblzujiyGce0twv0g", "tbl7HfsZ6TI4nhYKh", "tblcA6PcxYDNLjQRG"],
        "description": "## Welcome to the Content calendar template!\nThis template is designed to help you plan, schedule, and manage your team's content.\n\nHere are a few tips to help you make the most of it.\n\n* Everything in an Airtable [base](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics#base) is customizable, including this description! You can add, edit, or remove any [tables](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#table), [fields](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#field), [records](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#record), or [views](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314) to fit your needs.\n\n* The Campaign field in the Content pipeline table is a [linked record](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F206452848-Linking-to-Another-Document) field. This means that if you click on one of the blue tokens with the name of a related campaign, it'll open up an [expanded version](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F202576579-Expanding-records) of that campaign's record from the Campaigns table.\n\n* Use [filters](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F202624989-Guide-to-views#add_filters) to see just the records you want to see. For example, switch to the Live view in the Content pipeline table. In this view, a filter has been applied so that only posts marked as “Live” in the [single select](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F203229705-Guide-to-the-basic-field-types#single-select) Status field are visible.\n\n* Expand the [apps](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502434-Getting-started-building-blocks-for-success) dashboard to see visual writer pipelines, production timelines, and more.\n\nExplore our [template gallery](https:\u002F\u002Fairtable.com\u002Ftemplates) for other example bases, or check out our [guide to getting started in Airtable](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics) to learn how to build a new base from scratch!",
