        "description": "## Welcome to the Product planning template!\n\nThis template is based on a case study about how Automatic, a connected-car pioneer, uses Airtable. [Read more here.](https:\u002F\u002Fairtable.news\u002Fautomatics-approach-to-product-management-55d863a8f56a)\n\nHere are some tips to help you get the most out of it:\n\n* Everything in an Airtable [base](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics#base) is customizable, including this description! You can add, edit, or remove any [tables](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#table), [fields](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#field), [records](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#record), or [views](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314) to fit your needs.\n* The Stories table holds records for “stories,” or brief, high-level descriptions of a user’s specific requirements, written from their perspective. Try adding a new story record by clicking the plus button at the bottom of the list.\n* Each story record is [linked](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502354#h_0c3d1a65-1f35-4e67-9b14-6213d4d2bca9) through the Facet field to a record in the Facets table, which holds records with details about the app’s different facets. Try clicking one of the linked facets to quickly see more information about it.\n* The Open stories grid view is [filtered](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021501754-Getting-started-customizing-your-first-view#filters) to show stories that are not yet built. Try marking in the checkbox that a story has been built to filter it out of this view.\n* The Add story [form builder](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314#h_3579a188-40d6-4698-bc63-8515e29acc4a) lets you create a form that allows users to submit new stories. Try changing the filler logo above the form’s title to your own company’s logo.\n* Expand the [apps](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502434-Getting-started-building-blocks-for-success) dashboard for an open story counter and a search bar. You can also reference the \"Read me 👋\" [description app](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F115013405088-Description-block) at any time to find out more information.\n\nExplore our [template gallery](https:\u002F\u002Fairtable.com\u002Ftemplates) for other example bases, or check out our [guide to getting started in Airtable](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics) to learn how to build a new base from scratch!",
