        "description": "## Welcome to the Project tracker template!\nUse this template to make even the most complex projects manageable by consolidating all of your work in one place. \n\nHere are some tips to help you get the most out of it:\n* Everything in an Airtable [base](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics#base) is customizable, including this description! You can add, edit, or remove any [tables](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#table), [fields](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#field), [records](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#record), or [views](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314) to fit your needs.\n* The Design projects view holds records of this imaginary design team’s projects, past and present. Try adding a new project record by clicking the plus button at the bottom of the list.\n* Each design project record is [linked](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502354#h_0c3d1a65-1f35-4e67-9b14-6213d4d2bca9) to a record in the Clients table, which holds information about the design firm’s clients. Try clicking one of the linked records in the Client field to quickly see more information about it.\n* The Completed projects grid view is [filtered](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021501754-Getting-started-customizing-your-first-view#filters) to show projects that are checked in the Complete field. Try removing a record’s Complete check mark to filter it out of this view.\n* The Project [calendar](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314-Getting-started-view-types#h_09de72bb-b976-4ee9-b55b-fb382448dc41) shows a timeline of all projects. Try changing the view from monthly to weekly.\n* Expand the [apps](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502434-Getting-started-building-blocks-for-success) dashboard for a project bar graph, a Gantt chart, and a due date deadline. You can also reference the \"Read me 👋\" [description app](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F115013405088-Description-block) at any time to find out more information.\n\nExplore our [template gallery](https:\u002F\u002Fairtable.com\u002Ftemplates) for other example bases, or check out our [guide to getting started in Airtable](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics) to learn how to build a new base from scratch!",
