        "description": "## Welcome to the Digital video production template!\nThis template is loaded with customizable features that will keep your entire digital video team running in sync—from pre-production to post-production.\n\nHere are some tips to help you get the most out of it:\n\n* Everything in an Airtable [base](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics#base) is customizable, including this description! You can add, edit, or remove any [tables](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#table), [fields](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#field), [records](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#record), or [views](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314) to fit your needs.\n* The Video tracker table holds information about your digital video team’s projects, and makes use of several types of views. Try adding a new video record by clicking the plus button at the bottom of the list.\n* Use specialized views to manage different parts of your videos. Schedule shoots with a [calendar](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314#h_09de72bb-b976-4ee9-b55b-fb382448dc41); keep track of rights and clearances on a [kanban board](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314#h_fe5caf18-e280-4097-8a45-fd11216974b6); and choose between thumbnails in a virtual [gallery](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314#h_610b99ad-8481-432d-a95a-90050d1c1f23). You can even create a shareable pitch form using a [form builder](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314#h_3579a188-40d6-4698-bc63-8515e29acc4a)!\n* Features like [record grouping](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F221747587-Guide-to-grouped-records) can help you organize the multiple moving parts of video production. In the Shots table, navigate to All shots grouped view, which allows you to get into detail about the shots that make up each scene—from camera angle to equipment.\n* Add info about your production team to the Staff directory table, and quickly see what projects each person has worked on. Plus, with a [link](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F206452848-Linking-to-Another-Document) to the Props and equipment table, you can easily see if someone has a particular prop or camera you need.\n* Expand the [apps](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502434-Getting-started-building-blocks-for-success) dashboard for a production timeline, a budget chart, and a team management table. You can also reference the \"Read me 👋\" [description app](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F115013405088-Description-block) at any time to find out more information.\n\nExplore our [template gallery](https:\u002F\u002Fairtable.com\u002Ftemplates) for other example bases, or check out our [guide to getting started in Airtable](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics) to learn how to build a new base from scratch!",
