        "description": "## Welcome to the Product catalog template!\nUse this template as an interactive inventory of the items sold by your business—plus keep track of the vendors, designers, and clients you work with, and manage their orders.\n\nHere are some tips to help you get the most out of it:\n\n* Everything in an Airtable [base](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics#base) is customizable, including this description! You can add, edit, or remove any [tables](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#table), [fields](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#field), [records](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021333094-Getting-started-tables-records-and-fields#record), or [views](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502314) to fit your needs.\n* The Furniture table holds records for this imaginary interior design shop’s product inventory. Try adding a new furniture record by clicking the plus button at the bottom of the list.\n* Each record in the Client orders table is [linked](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502354#h_0c3d1a65-1f35-4e67-9b14-6213d4d2bca9) to the multiple items that make up that order. The Order line items table holds records of those items, along with related details. Try clicking one of the linked items for a particular client order to quickly see more information about that item.\n* Several of the tables use [rollup fields](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F202576519-Guide-to-formula-lookup-count-and-rollup-fields#rollup), which perform calculations using information from other linked tables. In the Client orders table, for example, the Order total cost rollup field adds up the cost of each Client order's constituent Order line items.\n* The [group records function](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F221747587-Guide-to-grouped-records) allows you to group records together based on one or more fields of your choosing. Check out the Items by type [view](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F202624989-Guide-to-views#whats_a_view) in the Furniture table, which groups records together based on type and whether or not the item is in stock.\n* Expand the [apps](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021502434-Getting-started-building-blocks-for-success) dashboard to see an invoice generator, a gross sales total, a bar graph visualizing your most lucrative items, and a table summarizing your products’ average prices. You can also reference the \"Read me 👋\" [description app](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F115013405088-Description-block) at any time to find out more information.\n\nExplore our [template gallery](https:\u002F\u002Fairtable.com\u002Ftemplates) for other example bases, or check out our [guide to getting started in Airtable](https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.airtable.com\u002Fhc\u002Fen-us\u002Farticles\u002F360021518753-Getting-started-starting-with-the-base-ics) to learn how to build a new base from scratch!",
